---
title: Sweet Heat Shrimp & Cauli Bowls with Cabbage-Carrot Rice & Pickled Cucumber
description: Saucy cauliflower is the star of this bowl, making it a perfect vegan dinner idea! Here, you’ll roast florets until crisp and golden, then coat them in a jammy, garlicky sweet-hot glaze. Nestle the saucy cauli over a steaming bowl of veggie-loaded rice with tangy pickled cukes on the side. This bowl’s got all the bold flavors you crave, without the meat: Witness the power of cauliflower!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/658c7794529576b8aa46b1e7-1a41b1fd.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/658c7794529576b8aa46b1e7.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-heat-shrimp-and-cauli-bowls-658c7794529576b8aa46b1e7
nutrition:
  calories: 680 kcal
  fat: 17 g
  saturated fat: 2.5 g
  carbohydrates: 89 g
  sugar: 37 g
  protein: 26 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 2020 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Mini Cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Cut @Cauliflower Florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Trim @Scallions{2}; mince whites and slice greens on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces. Trim and peel carrot; grate @Carrots{3%ounce}(shredded) on the largest holes of a #box grater{}.

Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Sugar{1/4%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @Salt{}. Set aside to pickle.

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Rinse @Shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Open package of shrimp and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #medium pan{} (large pan for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add shrimp or chicken in a single layer; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While cauliflower roasts, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @White Rice{1/2%cup}, 1 cup water (2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion greens; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce} and shredded carrot; cook, stirring occasionally, until scallions are slightly charred and veggies are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

In a second small bowl, whisk together half the cornstarch and ¼ cup cold water (all the @Cornstarch{1%tablespoon} and ½ cup cold water for 4 servings) until no lumps remain. Set aside.

> Use pan used for shrimp or chicken here.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Add ginger and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Apricot Jam{1%unit}, @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, cornstarch mixture, and as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and syrupy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce heat to low.

> TIP: Add water a splash at a time if sauce seems too thick.

When cauliflower is done roasting, add to pan with sauce; stir until thoroughly coated.

> Stir shrimp or chicken into sauce along with cauliflower.

Stir cabbage mixture into pot with rice.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with saucy cauliflower and pickled cucumber (draining first). Serve.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.